var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"location":"guide/#Guide","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Conceptual reference for topics that need more explanation than a docstring provides.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Pipeline-Architecture","page":"Guide","title":"Pipeline Architecture","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#The-steps-vector","page":"Guide","title":"The steps vector","text":"AnalysisConfig.steps is a composable list of AbstractSMLMConfig subtypes. The orchestrator in analysis.jl iterates through them sequentially, threading state between steps:\n\nDetectFitConfig (required first)\n        │ produces smld\n        ▼\n  ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n  │ FilterConfig       (0+ times)│\n  │ FrameConnectConfig (0-1)     │  ← Any order,\n  │ DriftCorrectConfig (0-1)     │    any combination\n  │ DensityFilterConfig(0+ times)│\n  │ RenderConfig       (0+ times)│\n  └─────────────────────────────┘\n\nThe only ordering constraint: DetectFitConfig must be first because it is the only step that produces a BasicSMLD from raw image data. All other steps receive and return an existing smld.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Two-level-dispatch","page":"Guide","title":"Two-level dispatch","text":"The pipeline operates at two levels:\n\nOrchestrator (analyze(data, AnalysisConfig)): Loops over steps, calls each step, threads smld state, and collects StepRecords into AnalysisInfo\nStep dispatch (analyze(smld, StepConfig)): Each step config type has its own analyze() method that does the actual work\n\nThe step-by-step workflow (analyze(smld, cfg)) already supports any config in any order — the orchestrator just automates the loop and collects metadata.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#State-threading","page":"Guide","title":"State threading","text":"The orchestrator maintains smld as the working state. Each step receives the current smld and returns an updated one. Additional state captured from specific steps:\n\nsmld_raw — from DetectFitConfig (pre-filter SMLD)\nsmld_connected — from FrameConnectConfig (tracks with multi-frame info)\ndrift_model — from DriftCorrectConfig (fitted drift polynomial)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Repeatable-and-optional-steps","page":"Guide","title":"Repeatable and optional steps","text":"FilterConfig: Can appear multiple times (coarse filter early, tighter filter after connection)\nRenderConfig: Can appear multiple times (different zooms, colormaps, or strategies)\nDensityFilterConfig: Can appear multiple times\nFrameConnectConfig and DriftCorrectConfig: Typically used once, but not enforced","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Config-provenance","page":"Guide","title":"Config provenance","text":"Config Defined in Notes\nDetectFitConfig SMLMAnalysis Wraps SMLMBoxer + GaussMLE internally\nFilterConfig SMLMAnalysis Pure SMLMAnalysis logic\nFrameConnectConfig SMLMAnalysis Wraps SMLMFrameConnection internally\nDriftCorrectConfig SMLMAnalysis Wraps SMLMDriftCorrection internally\nDensityFilterConfig SMLMAnalysis Pure SMLMAnalysis logic\nRenderConfig SMLMRender Re-exported via const RenderConfig = SMLMRender.RenderConfig\n\nSMLMAnalysis defines most step configs as thin wrappers that delegate to ecosystem packages. RenderConfig is the exception — it's used directly from SMLMRender. Extending the pipeline with a new upstream package follows the same wrapper pattern.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Adding-a-new-step","page":"Guide","title":"Adding a new step","text":"Define @kwdef struct YourConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig in src/steps/yourstep.jl\nImplement internal function yourstep(smld, cfg; outdir, step_number, verbose) returning (result, info_namedtuple)\nAdd dispatch: analyze(smld::BasicSMLD, cfg::YourConfig; kw...) = yourstep(smld, cfg; kw...)\nAdd elseif cfg isa YourConfig in both analyze() methods in analysis.jl (data-based and file-based)\nExport YourConfig from SMLMAnalysis.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Multi-Dataset-Architecture","page":"Guide","title":"Multi-Dataset Architecture","text":"SMLM acquisitions are often split into multiple datasets – either multiple files from the same sample or a single long movie divided into segments. SMLMAnalysis handles this natively.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Why-multi-dataset?","page":"Guide","title":"Why multi-dataset?","text":"Memory efficiency: Process one dataset at a time without loading all images\nDrift correction: Each dataset is corrected independently, then aligned via inter-dataset shifts\nFrame numbering: Frames are 1 to n_frames_per_dataset within each dataset, NOT global indices. This is required by SMLMDriftCorrection's Legendre polynomial normalization to [-1, 1]\nDataset tracking: Every emitter carries a dataset field so downstream steps know which dataset it belongs to","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Configuration","page":"Guide","title":"Configuration","text":"Dataset boundaries are encoded in the data structure, not user-specified integers:\n\n# In-memory: Vector{Array} defines dataset boundaries\nimage_stacks = [images1, images2, images3, images4]  # 4 datasets\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\n\n# Step-by-step: same Vector{Array} input\n(smld, info) = analyze(image_stacks, DetectFitConfig(camera=camera, boxsize=9))\n\n# File-based: MIC format auto-detects blocks as datasets\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [DetectFitConfig(path=\"data.h5\", h5_format=:mic), ...],\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(config)  # No data argument needed\n\n# Multiple files: one per dataset\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [DetectFitConfig(paths=[\"d1.h5\", \"d2.h5\", \"d3.h5\", \"d4.h5\"]), ...],\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(config)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#SMLD-structure","page":"Guide","title":"SMLD structure","text":"After detection and fitting, the combined SMLD has:\n\nsmld.n_frames = frames per dataset (not total)\nsmld.n_datasets = number of datasets\nEach emitter.dataset identifies its source dataset\nEach emitter.frame is relative to its dataset (1-based)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Drift-Correction-Modes","page":"Guide","title":"Drift Correction Modes","text":"DriftCorrectConfig supports two primary modes, controlled by the continuous flag.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Registered-mode-(continuousfalse,-default)","page":"Guide","title":"Registered mode (continuous=false, default)","text":"For multi-dataset acquisitions where datasets are spatially registered (e.g., the stage returns to approximately the same position between datasets):\n\nDriftCorrectConfig(\n    degree = 2,\n    continuous = false,\n    quality = :singlepass\n)\n\nEach dataset gets its own intra-dataset drift polynomial\nInter-dataset alignment via entropy optimization over spatial overlap\nWarns if inter-dataset shifts exceed intershift_threshold_nm (default 500nm)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Continuous-mode-(continuoustrue)","page":"Guide","title":"Continuous mode (continuous=true)","text":"For a single long acquisition split into chunks for processing:\n\n# Short acquisition (< 4000 frames): single polynomial\nDriftCorrectConfig(\n    degree = 5,\n    continuous = true,\n    n_chunks = 0\n)\n\n# Long acquisition: chunked\nDriftCorrectConfig(\n    degree = 3,\n    continuous = true,\n    chunk_frames = 4000\n)\n\nDrift accumulates continuously across chunks/datasets\nChunking recommended for > 4000 frames (chunk_frames=4000 is a reasonable maximum per chunk)\nHigher polynomial degree may be needed for complex drift patterns","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Quality-settings","page":"Guide","title":"Quality settings","text":":singlepass (default): Single entropy optimization pass. Fast and usually sufficient.\n:iterative: Iterates until convergence. Slower but may give better results for difficult drift patterns.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Auto-ROI","page":"Guide","title":"Auto ROI","text":"auto_roi=true (default) automatically selects a dense subregion for entropy estimation, which is faster and gives better signal for datasets with uneven emitter density.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Saving-and-Resuming","page":"Guide","title":"Saving and Resuming","text":"The functional pipeline supports saving intermediate state for later resume:","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#SMLD-checkpoints","page":"Guide","title":"SMLD checkpoints","text":"Save/load SMLD after expensive steps (detectfit) using HDF5:\n\n# Save after expensive detectfit\n(smld, info) = analyze(image_stacks, DetectFitConfig(camera=camera, boxsize=9))\nsave_smld(\"output/after_detectfit.h5\", smld)\n\n# Resume later - try different filter parameters\nsmld = load_smld(\"output/after_detectfit.h5\")\n(smld, _) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(300.0, Inf)))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Full-pipeline-state","page":"Guide","title":"Full pipeline state","text":"Save/load the complete pipeline state (SMLD, drift model, connected SMLD, etc.) using JLD2:\n\n# After running full pipeline\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\nsave_pipeline_state(\"output/pipeline.jld2\", result)\n\n# Resume later\nstate = load_pipeline_state(\"output/pipeline.jld2\")\nstate.smld              # Final SMLD\nstate.drift_model       # Drift model\nstate.smld_connected    # Connected SMLD","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Verbosity-Levels","page":"Guide","title":"Verbosity Levels","text":"Control output detail via the verbose field:\n\nLevel Constant Output\n0 Verbosity.SILENT Errors only\n1 Verbosity.PROGRESS Step names, counts, timing\n2 Verbosity.STANDARD + stats.md, basic figures (fit_quality, overlays, drift plots)\n3 Verbosity.DETAILED + diagnostic plots, per-filter breakdowns, localizationsperframe\n4 Verbosity.DEBUG + MP4 animations, frame-by-frame analysis\n\nSet via AnalysisConfig or step function keyword:\n\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(camera=cam, steps=[...], verbose=Verbosity.DETAILED)\n\n# Or per-step\n(smld, info) = analyze(data, DetectFitConfig(camera=cam); verbose=Verbosity.DEBUG)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Uncertainty-Calibration","page":"Guide","title":"Uncertainty Calibration","text":"Frame connection includes automatic uncertainty calibration, which compares reported CRLB uncertainties against observed frame-to-frame scatter.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Model","page":"Guide","title":"Model","text":"The calibration fits: observed_variance = A + B * CRLB_variance\n\nWhere:\n\nA (nm^2): Additive motion/vibration variance (sigma_motion = sqrt(A))\nB (dimensionless): CRLB scale factor (k = sqrt(B))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Corrected-uncertainties","page":"Guide","title":"Corrected uncertainties","text":"After calibration, each localization's uncertainty is corrected:\n\nsigma_corrected = sqrt(sigma_motion^2 + k^2 * sigma_CRLB^2)\n\nTrack recombination then uses weighted averaging with corrected uncertainties, giving properly calibrated combined positions.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Configuration-2","page":"Guide","title":"Configuration","text":"FrameConnectConfig(\n    calibrate = true,         # Enable calibration (default)\n    clamp_k_to_one = true,    # k >= 1 (CRLB is theoretical lower bound)\n    filter_high_chi2 = false, # Optional: remove tracks with high chi-squared pairs\n    chi2_filter_threshold = 6.0\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Interpreting-results","page":"Guide","title":"Interpreting results","text":"Mean chi-squared ~ 2.0: Uncertainties well-calibrated (expected for chi-squared(2) distribution)\nMean chi-squared > 2.5: Uncertainties underestimated (motion, vibration, double-emitter fits)\nMean chi-squared < 1.5: Uncertainties overestimated (conservative CRLB)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#I/O-Formats","page":"Guide","title":"I/O Formats","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Native-SMLD-format-(HDF5)","page":"Guide","title":"Native SMLD format (HDF5)","text":"Save and load localization results with full metadata:\n\nsave_smld(\"results.h5\", smld; source_file=\"data.h5\", drift_model=dm)\nsmld = load_smld(\"results.h5\")\nsmld_info(\"results.h5\")  # Quick summary without loading data\n\nThe HDF5 file stores emitter positions, uncertainties, camera calibration, drift model coefficients, and provenance information. Supports all emitter types including GaussMLE types with fitted PSF widths.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#SMART-microscope-H5","page":"Guide","title":"SMART microscope H5","text":"Import data from SMART microscope acquisitions:\n\nimages, info = load_smart_h5(\"acquisition.h5\")\ninfo = load_smart_h5_info(\"acquisition.h5\")  # Metadata only","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#MIC-format","page":"Guide","title":"MIC format","text":"Import data from MIC (MATLAB Instrument Control):\n\nimages, metadata = load_mic_h5(\"experiment.h5\")\ninfo = load_mic_h5_info(\"experiment.h5\")  # Metadata only\nblock = load_mic_h5_block(\"experiment.h5\", 1)  # Single block (memory efficient)\n\nBlock-based loading is automatic when using DetectFitConfig(path=..., h5_format=:mic).","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#File-based-detection","page":"Guide","title":"File-based detection","text":"DetectFitConfig supports loading directly from H5 files, avoiding the need to hold all images in memory:\n\n# Auto-detect format, MIC blocks become datasets\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [DetectFitConfig(path=\"data.h5\", h5_format=:mic), ...],\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(config)\n\n# Multiple files (one per dataset)\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [DetectFitConfig(paths=[\"d1.h5\", \"d2.h5\"]), ...],\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(config)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Multi-Target-Analysis","page":"Guide","title":"Multi-Target Analysis","text":"MultiTargetConfig orchestrates independent analysis pipelines for multiple color channels and produces composite multi-channel renders.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Configuration-3","page":"Guide","title":"Configuration","text":"Each channel gets its own AnalysisConfig and image data. The MultiTargetConfig ties them together with labels, colors, and composite rendering settings:\n\nmt = MultiTargetConfig(\n    labels = [:IgG, :C1q],\n    colors = [:red, :green],\n    render_zoom = 20,\n    render_strategies = [GaussianRender(), CircleRender()],\n    clip_percentile = 0.99,\n    outdir = \"output/cell1/\",\n)\n\n(result, info) = analyze([\n    (image_stacks_647, config_647),\n    (image_stacks_568, config_568),\n], mt)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Accessing-results","page":"Guide","title":"Accessing results","text":"result.smlds              # Vector{BasicSMLD}, one per channel\nresult[:IgG]              # Per-channel AnalysisResult\nresult[:IgG].smld         # Channel SMLD\ninfo.channels[:IgG]       # Per-channel AnalysisInfo\ninfo.composite_renders    # Vector{RenderInfo} from composite renders","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Output-structure","page":"Guide","title":"Output structure","text":"Multi-target analysis writes per-channel outputs and composite renders:\n\noutput/cell1/\n├── IgG/                  # Per-channel pipeline output\n│   ├── 01_detectfit/\n│   ├── 02_filter/\n│   └── ...\n├── C1q/\n│   └── ...\n├── composite/            # Multi-channel overlay renders\n│   ├── gaussianrender_20x.png\n│   └── circlerender_20x.png\n├── smld_IgG.h5           # Per-channel SMLD files\n├── smld_C1q.h5\n└── multi_target_config.toml","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Composite-rendering","page":"Guide","title":"Composite rendering","text":"For non-histogram strategies, clip_percentile (default 0.99) clips outlier intensities before normalization to improve contrast. Histogram overlays use saturate mode instead (count=1 = full brightness).","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Core-Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Core Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Verbosity-Levels","page":"API Reference","title":"Verbosity Levels","text":"Verbosity is a module with integer constants controlling output detail:\n\nLevel Constant Output\n0 Verbosity.SILENT Errors only\n1 Verbosity.PROGRESS Step names, counts, timing\n2 Verbosity.STANDARD + stats.md, basic figures\n3 Verbosity.DETAILED + diagnostic plots, per-filter breakdowns\n4 Verbosity.DEBUG + MP4 animations, frame-by-frame analysis","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Step-Configs","page":"API Reference","title":"Step Configs","text":"note: RenderConfig\nRenderConfig is re-exported from SMLMRender.jl and used directly as a step config. See SMLMRender documentation for details.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Multi-Target","page":"API Reference","title":"Multi-Target","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#I/O","page":"API Reference","title":"I/O","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Calibration","page":"API Reference","title":"Calibration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Utilities","page":"API Reference","title":"Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Internals","page":"API Reference","title":"Internals","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.SMLMAnalysis","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.SMLMAnalysis","text":"SMLMAnalysis\n\nHigh-level integration package for the JuliaSMLM ecosystem.\n\nProvides a unified analyze() API for SMLM analysis. The config type determines the operation via multiple dispatch:\n\nQuick Start\n\nusing SMLMAnalysis\n\n# Full pipeline with AnalysisConfig\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [\n        DetectFitConfig(boxsize=9, psf_model=:variable),\n        FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)),\n        DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2),\n        RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno),\n    ],\n    outdir = \"output/\",\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\n\n# Individual steps via analyze() dispatch\n(smld, info) = analyze(image_stacks, DetectFitConfig(camera=cam, boxsize=9))\n(smld, info) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)))\n(smld, info) = analyze(smld, DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2))\n(img, info)  = analyze(smld, RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno))\n\nRe-exported Types\n\nKey types from ecosystem packages are re-exported for convenience:\n\nSMLMData: AbstractCamera, IdealCamera, SCMOSCamera, BasicSMLD, Emitter types\nGaussMLE: GaussMLEConfig, PSF models, ROIBatch\nSMLMRender: render strategies\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.analyze","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.analyze","text":"analyze(data, cfg::DetectFitConfig; kwargs...) -> (smld, info)\n\nRun combined detection and fitting. Camera must be set in cfg.camera.\n\nArguments\n\ndata::Vector{<:AbstractArray{<:Real,3}}: Vector of image stacks (one per dataset)\ncfg::DetectFitConfig: Configuration (must include camera)\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(cfg::DetectFitConfig; kwargs...) -> (smld, info)\n\nFile-based detection and fitting. Requires cfg.path or cfg.paths and cfg.camera.\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(smld, cfg::FilterConfig; kwargs...) -> (filtered_smld, info)\n\nFilter localizations by quality criteria.\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(smld, cfg::FrameConnectConfig; kwargs...) -> (combined_smld, info)\n\nRun frame connection on localizations.\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(smld, cfg::DriftCorrectConfig; kwargs...) -> (corrected_smld, info)\n\nRun drift correction on localizations.\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(smld, cfg::DensityFilterConfig; kwargs...) -> (filtered_smld, info)\n\nFilter localizations by neighbor density.\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(smld, cfg::RenderConfig; kwargs...) -> (render_image, info)\n\nRender localizations to a super-resolution image.\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(data, config::AnalysisConfig) -> (AnalysisResult, AnalysisInfo)\n\nRun SMLM analysis pipeline defined by config.\n\nReturns a tuple of (AnalysisResult, AnalysisInfo) following the JuliaSMLM tuple-pattern.\n\nArguments\n\ndata: Image data - one of:\nVector{AbstractArray{<:Real,3}}: Multiple datasets (primary path)\nAbstractArray{<:Real,3}: Single dataset\nconfig: AnalysisConfig with camera, steps, and output settings\n\nExample\n\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [\n        DetectFitConfig(boxsize=9),\n        FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)),\n        DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2),\n        RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno),\n    ],\n    outdir = \"output/\",\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\nresult.smld               # Final SMLD\ninfo.steps[:detectfit]    # DetectFit step info\ninfo.steps[:driftcorrect] # Drift step info\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(data, steps::AbstractSMLMConfig...; camera, kwargs...) -> (AnalysisResult, AnalysisInfo)\n\nConvenience varargs form. Builds AnalysisConfig from positional step configs and keyword arguments.\n\nExample\n\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks,\n    DetectFitConfig(boxsize=9),\n    FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)),\n    DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2);\n    camera=cam, outdir=\"output/\")\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(config::AnalysisConfig) -> (AnalysisResult, AnalysisInfo)\n\nRun analysis from file paths specified in DetectFitConfig. No image data argument needed - data is loaded from files.\n\nExample\n\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [\n        DetectFitConfig(path=\"data.h5\"),\n        FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)),\n    ],\n    outdir = \"output/\",\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(config)\n\n\n\n\n\nanalyze(channels::Vector{<:Tuple}, config::MultiTargetConfig) -> (MultiTargetResult, MultiTargetInfo)\n\nRun independent analysis pipelines for each channel and produce composite renders.\n\nEach element of channels is a (data, AnalysisConfig) tuple where data is an image stack (or Vector of stacks) or file path. The config.labels must match the number of channels.\n\nArguments\n\nchannels: Vector of (data, AnalysisConfig) tuples, one per target/color\nconfig: MultiTargetConfig with labels, colors, rendering, and output settings\n\nReturns\n\n(MultiTargetResult, MultiTargetInfo) tuple following the JuliaSMLM convention.\n\nExample\n\nmt = MultiTargetConfig(\n    labels = [:IgG, :C1q],\n    colors = [:red, :green],\n    render_zoom = 20,\n    outdir = \"output/cell1/\",\n)\n\n(result, info) = analyze([\n    (image_stacks_647, config_647),\n    (image_stacks_568, config_568),\n], mt)\n\nresult.smlds              # Vector{BasicSMLD}\nresult[:IgG].smld         # Per-channel access\ninfo.channels[:IgG]       # Per-channel AnalysisInfo\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.AnalysisConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.AnalysisConfig","text":"AnalysisConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nComplete description of an SMLM analysis pipeline.\n\nThe steps vector contains upstream package configs (BoxerConfig, GaussMLEConfig, etc.) and SMLMAnalysis-specific configs (FilterConfig, DensityFilterConfig). The pipeline executes steps in order.\n\nFields\n\ncamera::AbstractCamera: Camera model (required, no default)\nsteps::Vector{SMLMData.AbstractSMLMConfig}: Ordered pipeline steps\nroi::Union{NamedTuple, Nothing}: Optional ROI as (x=100:300, y=50:200) to crop images/camera\noutdir::Union{String, Nothing}: Output directory for results\nverbose::Int: Verbosity level (default: STANDARD)\n\nExample\n\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [\n        DetectFitConfig(boxsize=9, psf_model=:variable),\n        FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)),\n        DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2),\n        RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno),\n    ],\n    outdir = \"output/\",\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.AnalysisResult","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.AnalysisResult","text":"AnalysisResult\n\nImmutable result from analyze(). Replaces the old mutable Analysis struct.\n\nFields\n\nsmld::BasicSMLD: Final SMLD after all steps\nsmld_connected::Union{BasicSMLD, Nothing}: Connected SMLD (if frameconnect was run)\ndrift_model::Any: Drift model (if driftcorrect was run)\n\nAccess\n\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\nresult.smld               # Final SMLD\nresult.drift_model        # Drift model for plotting\nresult.smld_connected     # Connected SMLD for track analysis\ninfo.steps[:driftcorrect] # Step info from upstream packages\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.AnalysisInfo","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.AnalysisInfo","text":"AnalysisInfo <: AbstractSMLMInfo\n\nAggregated metadata from all analysis steps, following the tuple-pattern.\n\nFields\n\nelapsed_s::Float64: Total elapsed time in seconds\nsteps::Dict{Symbol, Any}: Step name → upstream info struct mapping\nstep_records::Vector{StepRecord}: Full step history with timing and config\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.StepRecord","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.StepRecord","text":"StepRecord\n\nRecord of a completed pipeline step, stored in AnalysisInfo.\n\nFields\n\nnumber::Int: Step number in the pipeline\nname::String: Step name (derived from config type, e.g. \"filter\")\nconfig::AbstractSMLMConfig: The config used for this step\ntimestamp::DateTime: When the step completed\ntiming::Float64: Elapsed time in seconds\nsummary::Dict{Symbol, Any}: Summary statistics (counts, acceptance rates, etc.)\ninfo::Any: Upstream package info struct (BoxesInfo, FitInfo, DriftInfo, etc.)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.DataSource","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.DataSource","text":"DataSource\n\nLazy loading wrapper for SMLM image data. Supports:\n\nSingle 3D array (one dataset)\nVector of 3D arrays (multiple datasets, boundaries encoded in data structure)\nFile path for deferred loading\n\nConstructors\n\nDataSource(images)                          # From single 3D array (1 dataset)\nDataSource(image_stacks)                    # From Vector{Array} (N datasets)\nDataSource(path; frame_range=nothing)       # From file path (lazy)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.DetectFitConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.DetectFitConfig","text":"DetectFitConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nCombined detection and fitting step. Detects ROIs via SMLMBoxer and fits localizations via GaussMLE in a single step, with per-dataset processing.\n\nData Source Keywords (for file-based workflows)\n\npath: Single H5 file path\npaths: Vector of H5 file paths (one per dataset)\ndataset_frames: Explicit frame ranges per dataset\nh5_format: :auto, :smart, or :mic\n\nDetection Keywords\n\nboxsize: ROI size in pixels (default: 11)\nmin_photons: Detection threshold (default: 500.0)\npsf_sigma: Expected PSF width in microns (default: 0.135)\n\nFitting Keywords\n\npsf_model: :fixed, :variable, or :anisotropic (default: :variable)\niterations: MLE iterations (default: 20)\nbackend: :auto, :gpu, or :cpu (default: :auto)\n\nFilter Preview\n\nfilter_min_photons, filter_max_precision, filter_min_pvalue: Thresholds shown on fit quality plots (gray rejected regions). Set these to match your intended FilterConfig settings.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.FilterConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.FilterConfig","text":"FilterConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nQuality-based filtering of localizations. All criteria use (min, max) tuples.\n\nKeywords\n\nphotons: Photon count range, e.g. (500.0, Inf)\nprecision: Localization precision range in microns, e.g. (0.0, 0.007)\npvalue: Goodness-of-fit p-value range, e.g. (1e-3, 1.0)\npsf_sigma: PSF width filter. :auto uses mode ± 10%, or explicit (min, max) in microns\n\nAll filters default to nothing (disabled).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.FrameConnectConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.FrameConnectConfig","text":"FrameConnectConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nFrame connection step. Links localizations of the same emitter across consecutive frames using SMLMFrameConnection, then optionally calibrates uncertainties.\n\nKeywords\n\nmax_frame_gap: Maximum dark frames allowed in a track (default: 5)\nmax_sigma_dist: Spatial matching threshold in sigma (default: 5.0)\ncalibrate: Run uncertainty calibration after connection (default: true)\nclamp_k_to_one: Prevent CRLB scale factor k < 1 (default: true)\nfilter_high_chi2: Remove tracks with high chi-squared pairs (default: false)\nchi2_filter_threshold: Chi-squared threshold for track removal (default: 6.0)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.DriftCorrectConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.DriftCorrectConfig","text":"DriftCorrectConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nDrift correction step using entropy-based optimization from SMLMDriftCorrection.\n\nKeywords\n\ndegree: Polynomial degree for drift model (default: 2)\ncontinuous: true for continuous acquisition, false for registered multi-dataset (default: false)\nn_chunks: Split continuous data into N chunks, 0 = no chunking (default: 0)\nchunk_frames: Alternative chunking by frames per chunk (default: 0)\nquality: :singlepass (fast) or :iterative (default: :singlepass)\nauto_roi: Automatically select dense ROI for estimation (default: true)\nintershift_threshold_nm: Warning threshold for inter-dataset shifts (default: 500.0)\n\nSee the Guide for details on continuous vs registered modes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.DensityFilterConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.DensityFilterConfig","text":"DensityFilterConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nDensity-based filtering that removes isolated localizations lacking nearby neighbors.\n\nKeywords\n\nn_sigma: Search radius in localization uncertainty units (default: 2.0)\nmin_neighbors: Minimum neighbor count. :auto uses valley detection between isolated and clustered populations (default: :auto)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.MultiTargetConfig","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.MultiTargetConfig","text":"MultiTargetConfig <: AbstractSMLMConfig\n\nConfiguration for multi-target (multi-color) SMLM analysis.\n\nEach channel runs an independent analyze(data, AnalysisConfig) pipeline, then results are composited into multi-channel renders.\n\nFields\n\nlabels::Vector{Symbol}: Channel labels (e.g., [:IgG, :C1q])\ncolors::Vector{Symbol}: Colors per channel (default: automatic palette)\nrender_zoom::Float64: Zoom factor for composite renders\nrender_strategies::Vector{SMLMRender.RenderingStrategy}: Rendering strategies for composites\nclip_percentile::Union{Float64, Nothing}: Intensity clipping for composite renders (default: 0.99). Lower values (e.g., 0.95) increase contrast for sparse data. nothing for saturate mode.\noutdir::String: Output directory\nverbose::Int: Verbosity level\n\nExample\n\nmt = MultiTargetConfig(\n    labels = [:IgG, :C1q],\n    colors = [:red, :green],\n    render_zoom = 20,\n    outdir = \"output/cell1/\",\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.MultiTargetResult","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.MultiTargetResult","text":"MultiTargetResult\n\nResult of a multi-target analysis. Holds per-channel AnalysisResult objects and the final SMLD vectors for composite rendering.\n\nFields\n\nlabels::Vector{Symbol}: Channel labels in order\nsmlds::Vector{SMLMData.BasicSMLD}: Per-channel SMLD results\nchannels::Dict{Symbol, AnalysisResult}: Per-channel results\nchannel_registration::Any: Reserved for future registration transforms\noutdir::String: Output directory\n\nIndexing\n\nresult[:IgG]         # Access per-channel AnalysisResult\nkeys(result)         # Channel labels\nresult.smlds         # Vector of all SMLDs\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.MultiTargetInfo","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.MultiTargetInfo","text":"MultiTargetInfo <: AbstractSMLMInfo\n\nAggregated metadata from a multi-target analysis.\n\nFields\n\nelapsed_s::Float64: Total elapsed time in seconds\nchannels::Dict{Symbol, AnalysisInfo}: Per-channel analysis info\ncomposite_renders::Vector{SMLMRender.RenderInfo}: Info from composite renders\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.save_smld","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.save_smld","text":"save_smld(filepath::String, smld::BasicSMLD;\n          source_file::Union{String,Nothing}=nothing,\n          drift_model=nothing,\n          compression::Int=3)\n\nSave BasicSMLD to HDF5 file with full metadata for reproducibility.\n\nSupports all emitter types including GaussMLE types with fitted PSF widths:\n\nEmitter2DFitSigma: saves fitted σ (isotropic PSF width)\nEmitter2DFitSigmaXY: saves fitted σx, σy (anisotropic PSF widths)\n\nArguments\n\nfilepath: Output .h5 file path\nsmld: BasicSMLD object to save\nsource_file: Original data file path (for provenance tracking)\ndrift_model: Optional drift correction model (LegendrePolynomial, etc.)\ncompression: HDF5 compression level 0-9 (default: 3)\n\nFile Structure\n\n/metadata           - Format version, package info, timestamps\n/emitters           - Columnar emitter data (x, y, z, photons, psf_sigma_x, etc.)\n/camera             - Camera type and calibration\n/drift_correction   - Drift model coefficients (if provided)\n/provenance         - Source file info\n\nExample\n\nsave_smld(\"results.h5\", smld; source_file=\"/data/experiment.h5\", drift_model=dm)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_smld","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_smld","text":"load_smld(filepath::String) -> BasicSMLD\n\nLoad BasicSMLD from HDF5 file.\n\nReturns a BasicSMLD with the saved emitters, camera, and metadata. Automatically reconstructs the correct emitter type (including GaussMLE types with PSF width fields).\n\nDrift correction info is stored in metadata[\"drift_correction\"] if present.\n\nExample\n\nsmld = load_smld(\"results.h5\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.smld_info","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.smld_info","text":"smld_info(filepath::String)\n\nPrint summary info about an SMLD HDF5 file without loading all data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.save_pipeline_state","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.save_pipeline_state","text":"save_pipeline_state(path::String, result::AnalysisResult;\n                    smld_raw=nothing, step_records=StepRecord[], camera=nothing)\n\nSave pipeline state to JLD2 for cross-session resume.\n\nExample\n\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\nsave_pipeline_state(\"output/checkpoint.jld2\", result;\n    step_records=info.step_records, camera=config.camera)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_pipeline_state","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_pipeline_state","text":"load_pipeline_state(path::String) -> NamedTuple\n\nLoad pipeline state from JLD2.\n\nReturns a NamedTuple with fields: smld, smldraw, smldconnected, driftmodel, steprecords, camera.\n\nExample\n\nstate = load_pipeline_state(\"output/checkpoint.jld2\")\nsmld = state.smld\n# Continue pipeline from here\n(smld, info) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_smart_h5","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_smart_h5","text":"load_smart_h5(filepath::String; frame_range=nothing)\n\nLoad image data from a SMART microscope HDF5 file.\n\nArguments\n\nfilepath::String: Path to the HDF5 file\nframe_range: Optional range of frames to load (e.g., 1:1000). If nothing, loads all frames.\n\nReturns\n\ndata::Array{UInt16, 3}: Image data (width, height, frames)\n\nExample\n\n# Load all frames\ndata = load_smart_h5(\"data/experiment.h5\")\n\n# Load first 1000 frames\ndata = load_smart_h5(\"data/experiment.h5\", frame_range=1:1000)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_smart_h5_info","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_smart_h5_info","text":"load_smart_h5_info(filepath::String)\n\nLoad metadata about a SMART microscope HDF5 file without reading the full dataset.\n\nReturns a NamedTuple with:\n\nfilepath: Full path to the file\nwidth, height, nframes: Image dimensions\ndtype: Data type of the images\nfilesizegb: Approximate file size in GB\n\nExample\n\ninfo = load_smart_h5_info(\"data/gatta_ruler/2025-10-23/20R-ruler-0.1exp-TIRF-onlyZFocusLockDT1-1ch--2025-10-23_11-29-25.h5\")\nprintln(\"File contains \", info.nframes, \" frames of size \", info.width, \"x\", info.height)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_smart_h5_frame","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_smart_h5_frame","text":"load_smart_h5_frame(filepath::String, frame::Int)\n\nLoad a single frame from a SMART microscope HDF5 file.\n\nArguments\n\nfilepath::String: Path to the HDF5 file\nframe::Int: Frame number to load (1-indexed)\n\nReturns\n\nframe_data::Matrix{UInt16}: Single frame image\n\nExample\n\nframe1 = load_smart_h5_frame(\"data/experiment.h5\", 1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.smart_h5_to_array","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.smart_h5_to_array","text":"smart_h5_to_array(filepath::String; max_frames=nothing)\n\nLoad SMART microscope data as a properly formatted array for SMLM processing.\n\nThis function transposes the data from (width, height, frames) to (height, width, frames) to match standard image conventions where the first dimension is rows (y) and second is columns (x).\n\nArguments\n\nfilepath::String: Path to the HDF5 file\nmax_frames: Optional maximum number of frames to load\n\nReturns\n\ndata::Array{UInt16, 3}: Image data in (rows, cols, frames) format\ninfo::NamedTuple: File metadata\n\nExample\n\ndata, info = smart_h5_to_array(\"data/experiment.h5\", max_frames=1000)\nprintln(\"Loaded \", size(data, 3), \" frames of size \", size(data, 1), \"x\", size(data, 2))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5","text":"load_mic_h5(filepath; max_frames=nothing, max_blocks=nothing) -> images, dataset_indices\n\nLoad MIC dSTORM H5 file. Each block becomes a \"dataset\".\n\nReturns:\n\nimages: 3D array (height × width × n_frames)\ndataset_indices: Vector{Int} mapping each frame to its block (1-indexed)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_info","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_info","text":"load_mic_h5_info(filepath) -> NamedTuple\n\nGet info about MIC H5 file without loading all data.\n\nReturns NamedTuple with fields:\n\nheight, width: image dimensions\nn_frames: total frames across all blocks\nn_blocks: number of data blocks (datasets)\nframesperblock: Vector of frame counts per block\nhas_calibration: whether calibration data exists\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_block","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_block","text":"load_mic_h5_block(filepath, block_num::Int) -> Array{Float32,3}\n\nLoad a single data block from MIC H5 file. block_num is 1-indexed.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_calibration","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_calibration","text":"load_mic_h5_calibration(filepath) -> NamedTuple\n\nLoad calibration data from MIC H5 file.\n\nReturns NamedTuple with (offset, variance, gain) as 2D arrays.\n\nNOTE: The gain in MIC H5 files is INVERTED compared to our convention. Our convention: ADU = photons * gain, so gain ≈ 0.24 e-/ADU MIC H5: gain stored as ~4, which is 1/gain in our convention Use loadmich5calibrationfor_scmos() to get corrected values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_calibration_for_scmos","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.load_mic_h5_calibration_for_scmos","text":"load_mic_h5_calibration_for_scmos(filepath) -> NamedTuple\n\nLoad calibration data and convert to SCMOSCamera convention.\n\nReturns NamedTuple with:\n\noffset: per-pixel offset (unchanged)\nreadnoise: per-pixel readnoise (sqrt of variance)\ngain: per-pixel gain (INVERTED from stored value)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.analyze_frameconnect_drift","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.analyze_frameconnect_drift","text":"analyze_frameconnect_drift(smld_connected) -> NamedTuple\n\nAnalyze frame-to-frame drift from linked localizations.\n\nFor multi-dataset analysis, drift is calculated per dataset since frame numbers reset between datasets and datasets may be acquired at different times.\n\nReturns NamedTuple with:\n\nframeshifts: Dict{Int, Vector} mapping datasetid => shifts per frame transition\nchi2_values: Vector of χ² values for each pair (should follow χ²(2) if uncertainties correct)\nmean_chi2: Mean χ² (expected = 2 for correct uncertainties)\nnpairstotal: Total number of frame-to-frame pairs analyzed\nn_datasets: Number of datasets with tracked emitters\ncalibration: Fitted calibration model (A, B, uncertainties, R²)\nstage_motion: Stage motion estimates\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.apply_uncertainty_calibration","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.apply_uncertainty_calibration","text":"apply_uncertainty_calibration(smld_connected, σ_motion, k_scale) -> (smld_connected_corrected, smld_combined)\n\nApply uncertainty calibration to connected localizations and recombine tracks.\n\nThe calibration model is: σ²corrected = σ²motion + k² × σ²_CRLB\n\nFor each localization:\n\nσxcorrected = √(σmotion² + k² × σx²)\nσycorrected = √(σmotion² + k² × σy²)\n\nThen recombines tracks using weighted averaging with corrected uncertainties.\n\nReturns:\n\nsmldconnectedcorrected: Connected localizations with corrected uncertainties\nsmld_combined: Recombined tracks with corrected uncertainties\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.recombine_tracks","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.recombine_tracks","text":"recombine_tracks(smld_connected) -> BasicSMLD\n\nRecombine localizations into tracks using weighted averaging.\n\nGroups localizations by track_id and computes weighted average position and combined uncertainty for each track.\n\nThe combined emitter uses:\n\nPosition: weighted average (weight = 1/σ²)\nUncertainty: σ_combined = 1/√(Σ 1/σ²)\nFrame: middle frame of track\nPhotons: sum of photons\nBackground: mean background\npvalue: geometric mean of pvalues\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.crop_camera","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.crop_camera","text":"crop_camera(camera::AbstractCamera, roi_x::UnitRange, roi_y::UnitRange)\n\nCrop camera to specified pixel ROI while preserving physical coordinates.\n\nReturns a new camera with:\n\npixeledgesx/y sliced to cover ROI (preserves original μm positions)\nFor SCMOSCamera: offset/gain/readnoise/qe matrices cropped accordingly\n\nArguments\n\ncamera: Original camera\nroi_x: Pixel range in x (columns), e.g., 100:300\nroi_y: Pixel range in y (rows), e.g., 50:200\n\nExample\n\ncam = IdealCamera(512, 512, 0.1)\ncam_cropped = crop_camera(cam, 100:300, 50:200)\n# cam_cropped.pixel_edges_x[1] = 10.0 μm (not 0!)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.crop_images","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.crop_images","text":"crop_images(images::AbstractArray{T,3}, roi_x::UnitRange, roi_y::UnitRange) where T\n\nCrop image stack to specified pixel ROI.\n\nArguments\n\nimages: 3D array (y, x, frames) - Julia convention: [row, col]\nroi_x: Pixel range in x (columns)\nroi_y: Pixel range in y (rows)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.step_name","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.step_name","text":"step_name(cfg::AbstractSMLMConfig) -> String\n\nDerive step name from config type (e.g., FilterConfig → \"filter\", DriftCorrectConfig → \"driftcorrect\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.step_outdir","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.step_outdir","text":"step_outdir(outdir, step_number, cfg) -> Union{String, Nothing}\n\nCompute output directory for a step: outdir/02_filter/. Returns nothing if outdir is nothing.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.n_datasets","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.n_datasets","text":"n_datasets(ds::DataSource) -> Int\n\nNumber of datasets in this data source.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.n_frames_per_dataset","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.n_frames_per_dataset","text":"n_frames_per_dataset(ds::DataSource) -> Int\n\nFrames per dataset. For Vector{Array}, uses first element.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.TeeLogger","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.TeeLogger","text":"TeeLogger(loggers)\n\nLogger that forwards messages to multiple loggers. Used internally to tee @info output to both console and log file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._analyze_and_calibrate-Tuple{BasicSMLD, BasicSMLD, FrameConnectConfig, Dict{Symbol, Any}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._analyze_and_calibrate","text":"_analyze_and_calibrate(smld_connected, smld_combined, cfg, summary) -> (calibrated_smld, drift_analysis)\n\nRun uncertainty calibration on connected tracks. Pure function – returns the calibrated SMLD and drift analysis result without mutating anything except the summary dict (for logging).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._apply_roi-Tuple{Vector{<:AbstractArray{<:Real, 3}}, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._apply_roi","text":"Apply ROI cropping to data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._calc_inter_shifts-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._calc_inter_shifts","text":"Calculate inter-dataset shift magnitudes in nm (Euclidean distance)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._calc_max_drift-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._calc_max_drift","text":"Calculate max intra-dataset drift using drift_trajectory\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._calculate_mode-Union{Tuple{Vector{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T<:Real","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._calculate_mode","text":"_calculate_mode(values; n_bins=100)\n\nCalculate the mode of a distribution using histogram binning. Returns the center of the most populated bin.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._columnar_to_smld-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._columnar_to_smld","text":"Reconstruct SMLD from columnar format.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._construct_emitters-Tuple{String, Type, Int64, Bool, Vararg{Any, 21}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._construct_emitters","text":"_construct_emitters(...)\n\nInternal: Construct emitters of the appropriate type based on emittertypestr.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._copy_emitter_with_uncertainty-Tuple{GaussMLE.Emitter2DFitGaussMLE, Float32, Float32}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._copy_emitter_with_uncertainty","text":"Copy emitter with new σx and σy values. Works for any GaussMLE emitter type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._create_combined_emitter-Tuple{GaussMLE.Emitter2DFitGaussMLE, Vararg{Any, 10}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._create_combined_emitter","text":"Create combined emitter from weighted average. Works for any GaussMLE emitter type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._default_colors-Tuple{Int64}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._default_colors","text":"_default_colors(n::Int) -> Vector{Symbol}\n\nDefault color palette for multi-target rendering. Supports up to 6 channels; provide explicit colors for more.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._detect_h5_format-Tuple{String}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._detect_h5_format","text":"Detect H5 file format by checking internal structure\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._detectfit_box_color-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._detectfit_box_color","text":"Determine box color based on fit status (like fit.jl)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._empty_emitters-Tuple{String, Type, Bool}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._empty_emitters","text":"_empty_emitters(emitter_type_str, T, is_3d)\n\nInternal: Create empty emitter vector of appropriate type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._estimate_bleaching_rate-Tuple{Vector{Int64}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._estimate_bleaching_rate","text":"Estimate observed bleaching rate from localizations per frame decay. Fits N(t) = a + bexp(-kt) using Nelder-Mead optimization.\n\nInitial guess from linearized fit: estimate offset from tail, then linear regression on log(N - offset) to get b and k. Nelder-Mead refines all three parameters.\n\nNote: This gives the OBSERVED decay rate, not the true kbleach for GenericFluor. Since bleaching only occurs from the On state:     kobserved = kbleach * Pon     where Pon = kon/(kon+koff) is the duty cycle\n\nTo get true kbleach: kbleach = kobserved / Pon\n\nReturns (kbleach, N0, offset, halflife, rsquared) or nothing if fit fails.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._estimate_koff-Tuple{Vector{Int64}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._estimate_koff","text":"Estimate koff from track length distribution. For geometric distribution: mean = 1/koff, so k_off = 1/mean\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._filter_high_chi2_tracks-Tuple{Any, Float64}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._filter_high_chi2_tracks","text":"_filter_high_chi2_tracks(smld_connected, threshold) -> (filtered_connected, filtered_combined, n_removed)\n\nRemove tracks that have any frame-to-frame pair with chi² > threshold. These are likely double-emitter fits where position shifts between frames.\n\nReturns filtered smld_connected, recombined smld, and count of removed tracks.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._fit_uncertainty_calibration-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._fit_uncertainty_calibration","text":"_fit_uncertainty_calibration(pair_data) -> NamedTuple\n\nFit uncertainty calibration model: observedvariance = A + B * CRLBvariance\n\nUses weighted least squares on raw data points (weight = 1/reported_var²) since Var(Δ²) ∝ σ⁴. Binned data is computed separately for plotting only.\n\nReturns NamedTuple with:\n\nA: additive term (nm²) - represents motion/vibration variance\nB: multiplicative factor - CRLB scale correction\nAσ, Bσ: uncertainties on A and B\nr_squared: goodness of fit\nbincenters, binobserved, bin_expected: binned data for plotting\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._get_gaussmle_emitter_types-Tuple{}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._get_gaussmle_emitter_types","text":"_get_gaussmle_emitter_types()\n\nInternal: Try to get GaussMLE emitter types if the package is loaded. Returns nothing if GaussMLE is not available.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._get_psf_sigma_bounds-Tuple{Any, Vector}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._get_psf_sigma_bounds","text":"_get_psf_sigma_bounds(range_spec, values) -> (lo, hi)\n\nCalculate PSF sigma filter bounds.\n\n:auto → mode ± 10%\n(min, max) → explicit bounds in microns\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._grid_figure_size-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._grid_figure_size","text":"_grid_figure_size(data; n_cols=4, n_rows=3, panel_height=200)\n\nCalculate figure size for grid overlay plots based on data aspect ratio.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._inject_camera-Tuple{DetectFitConfig, SMLMData.AbstractCamera}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._inject_camera","text":"_inject_camera(cfg::DetectFitConfig, camera::AbstractCamera) -> DetectFitConfig\n\nInject camera into DetectFitConfig if not already set. Used by AnalysisConfig pipeline.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._load_source-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._load_source","text":"Load images from a data source\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._normalize_data-Tuple{Vector{<:AbstractArray{<:Real, 3}}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._normalize_data","text":"Normalize input data to Vector{AbstractArray{<:Real,3}} for uniform processing.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._resolve_file_sources-Tuple{DetectFitConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._resolve_file_sources","text":"Resolve file-based sources from config options.\n\nReturns a vector of NamedTuples describing each dataset to load. Dataset count is determined from the data structure, not from a config field.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_box_overlay-NTuple{5, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_box_overlay","text":"_save_box_overlay(dir, filename, images, roi_batch, box_colors; title_prefix=\"Frame\")\n\nSave frame overlay with colored boxes around ROIs.\n\nArguments\n\ndir: Output directory\nfilename: Output filename (e.g., \"detection_overlay.png\")\nimages: 3D array of frame images\nroi_batch: ROIBatch with xcorners, ycorners, frame_indices\nbox_colors: Vector of colors, one per ROI (same order as roi_batch)\ntitle_prefix: Prefix for frame titles (default \"Frame\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_config!-Tuple{String, AbstractSMLMConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_config!","text":"Save step config to config.toml in the step output directory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_continuous_drift_figure-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_continuous_drift_figure","text":"Plot drift trajectory with global frame view for multi-dataset acquisitions. Uses drift_trajectory default mode (inter + intra per chunk) so boundary discontinuities between chunks are visible as gaps.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_detectfit_detailed-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_detectfit_detailed","text":"Generate detailed plots for DETAILED verbosity\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_detectfit_overlays-NTuple{6, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_detectfit_overlays","text":"Generate overlay plots showing detection boxes colored by fit status. Uses sample frames spread across all datasets with absolute frame labels.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_drift_jitter_plot-Tuple{Any, Any, Int64}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_drift_jitter_plot","text":"Plot frame-to-frame drift/jitter estimated from linked emitters. Shows both instantaneous shifts and cumulative drift using global frame index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_drift_model!-Tuple{Any, Any, Int64}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_drift_model!","text":"_save_drift_model!(group, dm::LegendrePolynomial, compression)\n\nSave LegendrePolynomial drift model to HDF5 group.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_info!-Tuple{String, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_info!","text":"_save_info!(dir::String, info; section::String=\"\")\n\nWrite upstream Info struct fields to info.toml in TOML format.\n\nWrites scalar fields (numbers, bools, strings, symbols, tuples of scalars). Skips complex fields (arrays, dicts, structs like BasicSMLD, models).\n\nWhen section is empty, writes a fresh file with type header. When section is provided, appends a [section] block.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._save_multitarget_config!-Tuple{MultiTargetConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._save_multitarget_config!","text":"_save_multitarget_config!(config::MultiTargetConfig)\n\nSerialize MultiTargetConfig to TOML file in the output directory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._smld_to_columnar-Tuple{Union{Nothing, BasicSMLD}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._smld_to_columnar","text":"Convert SMLD emitters to columnar format for fast JLD2 serialization. Returns a NamedTuple with arrays for each field.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._valley_threshold-Tuple{Vector{Int64}}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._valley_threshold","text":"Find threshold using valley detection between isolated (low neighbors) and clustered (high neighbors).\n\nAlgorithm:\n\nBuild and smooth histogram\nFind rightmost significant peak (clustered population)\nFind local minimum (valley) between origin and that peak\nIf no clear valley (unimodal), use heuristics based on peak position\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._with_dataset-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Emitter2DFit{T}, Int64}} where T","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._with_dataset","text":"Update emitter's dataset field using struct reconstruction\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._with_log_file-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._with_log_file","text":"_with_log_file(f, outdir)\n\nRun f() with @info output teed to outdir/log.txt. If outdir is nothing, just runs f() directly.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis._write_info_field!-Tuple{IO, Symbol, Number}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis._write_info_field!","text":"Write a single field to info.toml, skipping complex types.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.densityfilter_step-Tuple{BasicSMLD, DensityFilterConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.densityfilter_step","text":"densityfilter_step(smld, cfg; outdir=nothing, step_number=0, verbose=Verbosity.STANDARD)\n\nFilter localizations by neighbor density. Returns (filtered_smld, info).\n\nArguments\n\nsmld::BasicSMLD: Input localizations\ncfg::DensityFilterConfig: Density filter parameters\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\noutdir: Output directory (nothing to skip file output)\nstep_number: Step number for output directory naming\nverbose: Verbosity level\n\nReturns\n\n(filtered_smld, (step_record, n_before, n_after, threshold))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.detectfit-Tuple{AbstractArray{<:Real, 3}, SMLMData.AbstractCamera, DetectFitConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.detectfit","text":"detectfit(images::AbstractArray{<:Real,3}, camera, cfg; kwargs...) -> (smld, info)\n\nConvenience method for a single image stack. Wraps into a 1-element vector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.detectfit-Tuple{SMLMData.AbstractCamera, DetectFitConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.detectfit","text":"detectfit(camera, cfg; kwargs...) -> (smld, info)\n\nFile-based detectfit. Loads image data from cfg.path or cfg.paths. Each data source is loaded one at a time for memory efficiency.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.detectfit-Tuple{Vector{<:AbstractArray{<:Real, 3}}, SMLMData.AbstractCamera, DetectFitConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.detectfit","text":"detectfit(data, camera, cfg; kwargs...) -> (smld, info)\n\nRun combined detection and fitting on image data.\n\nArguments\n\ndata::Vector{<:AbstractArray{<:Real,3}}: Vector of image stacks (one per dataset)\ncamera::AbstractCamera: Camera model\ncfg::DetectFitConfig: Detection and fitting configuration\n\nKeywords\n\noutdir::Union{String,Nothing}=nothing: Output directory for results\nstep_number::Int=1: Step number in the pipeline\nverbose::Int=Verbosity.STANDARD: Verbosity level\n\nReturns\n\n(smld::BasicSMLD, info::NamedTuple) where info contains:\n\nstep_record::StepRecord: Step record with timing and summary\nboxes_info::Vector: Per-dataset BoxesInfo from SMLMBoxer\nfit_info::Vector: Per-dataset FitInfo from GaussMLE\nelapsed_s::Float64: Total elapsed time\nsmld_raw::BasicSMLD: Reference to the raw SMLD (same as smld)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.driftcorrect_step-Tuple{BasicSMLD, DriftCorrectConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.driftcorrect_step","text":"driftcorrect_step(smld, cfg; outdir, step_number, verbose) -> (corrected_smld, info_nt)\n\nRun drift correction on smld, returning the corrected SMLD as the primary result, plus a NamedTuple with step metadata.\n\nReturns\n\n(corrected_smld, (step_record, drift_model, drift_info))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.filter_step-Tuple{BasicSMLD, FilterConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.filter_step","text":"filter_step(smld, cfg; smld_raw=nothing, outdir=nothing, step_number=0, verbose=Verbosity.STANDARD)\n\nFilter localizations by quality criteria. Returns (filtered_smld, info).\n\nArguments\n\nsmld::BasicSMLD: Input localizations\ncfg::FilterConfig: Filter criteria\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nsmld_raw: Original unfiltered SMLD for detailed output diagnostics\noutdir: Output directory (nothing to skip file output)\nstep_number: Step number for output directory naming\nverbose: Verbosity level\n\nReturns\n\n(filtered_smld, (step_record, n_before, n_after))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.frameconnect_step-Tuple{BasicSMLD, FrameConnectConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.frameconnect_step","text":"frameconnect_step(smld, cfg; outdir, step_number, verbose) -> (combined_smld, info_nt)\n\nRun frame connection on smld, returning the combined (recombined) SMLD as the primary result, plus a NamedTuple with step metadata.\n\nReturns\n\n(combined_smld, (step_record, smld_connected, calibration_result, connect_info))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SMLMAnalysis.render_step-Tuple{BasicSMLD, RenderConfig}","page":"API Reference","title":"SMLMAnalysis.render_step","text":"render_step(smld, cfg; outdir=nothing, step_number=0, verbose=Verbosity.STANDARD)\n\nRender localizations to a super-resolution image. Returns (render_image, info).\n\nArguments\n\nsmld::BasicSMLD: Input localizations\ncfg::SMLMRender.RenderConfig: Render configuration\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\noutdir: Output directory (nothing to skip file output)\nstep_number: Step number for output directory naming\nverbose: Verbosity level\n\nReturns\n\n(render_image, (step_record, render_info))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SMLMAnalysis.jl","page":"Home","title":"SMLMAnalysis.jl","text":"High-level integration package for the JuliaSMLM ecosystem. Orchestrates detection, fitting, filtering, frame connection, drift correction, density filtering, rendering, and Bayesian grouping into reproducible SMLM analysis pipelines.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Two-Workflow-Patterns","page":"Home","title":"Two Workflow Patterns","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Config-driven-(production)","page":"Home","title":"Config-driven (production)","text":"# Steps are composable — reorder, repeat, or omit freely after DetectFitConfig\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = cam,\n    steps = [\n        DetectFitConfig(boxsize=9, psf_model=:variable),\n        FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)),\n        DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2),\n        RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno),\n    ],\n    outdir = \"output/\",\n)\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Step-by-step-(exploration)","page":"Home","title":"Step-by-step (exploration)","text":"(smld, df_info) = analyze(image_stacks, DetectFitConfig(camera=camera, boxsize=9))\nsmld_raw = df_info.smld_raw\n\n(smld, _) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf)); smld_raw=smld_raw)\n(smld, _) = analyze(smld, FrameConnectConfig(max_frame_gap=5))\n(smld, _) = analyze(smld, DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2))\n(img, _)  = analyze(smld, RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno))\n\n# Save intermediate state for later resume\nsave_smld(\"after_detectfit.h5\", smld)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Documentation","text":"Tutorial – Full pipeline walkthrough with figures at every step\nGuide – Concepts: multi-dataset architecture, drift modes, I/O\nAPI Reference – Complete function and type documentation","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"SMLMAnalysis\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Ecosystem","page":"Home","title":"Ecosystem","text":"SMLMData (core types)\n    |\n    +-- SMLMBoxer (ROI detection)\n    +-- GaussMLE (GPU-accelerated MLE fitting)\n    +-- SMLMFrameConnection (linking across frames)\n    +-- SMLMDriftCorrection (entropy-based drift correction)\n    +-- SMLMRender (super-resolution rendering)\n    +-- SMLMSim (simulation + image generation)\n    +-- MicroscopePSFs (PSF models)\n    +-- SMLMBaGoL (Bayesian grouping)\n    |\n    +-- SMLMAnalysis (integrates all)\n\n","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Tutorial","page":"Tutorial","title":"Tutorial","text":"This walkthrough runs a complete SMLM analysis pipeline on simulated data, showing the output at every step. All figures are generated from the examples/analysis_example.jl and examples/stepwise_example.jl scripts.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Setup","page":"Tutorial","title":"Setup","text":"using SMLMAnalysis\nusing MicroscopePSFs\n\n# Camera: 256x128 pixels @ 100nm\ncamera = IdealCamera(256, 128, 0.1)\n\n# Simulate: 4 datasets x 2000 frames, 8-mer pattern\nsim_params = StaticSMLMConfig(density=2.0, sigma_psf=0.13, nframes=2000, ndatasets=4)\npattern = Nmer2D(n=8, d=0.05)\nfluor = GenericFluor(photons=50000.0, k_off=20.0, k_on=0.02)\n\n(_, sim_info) = simulate(sim_params; pattern=pattern, molecule=fluor, camera=camera)\n\nImage generation uses gen_images from SMLMSim with a Gaussian PSF model. See the example scripts for the full setup including the per-dataset image generation workaround.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#AnalysisConfig-Approach","page":"Tutorial","title":"AnalysisConfig Approach","text":"The primary interface uses AnalysisConfig to define a complete pipeline:\n\nconfig = AnalysisConfig(\n    camera = camera,\n    steps = [\n        DetectFitConfig(boxsize=7, psf_sigma=0.13, psf_model=:variable),\n        FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf), precision=(0.0, 0.007), pvalue=(1e-3, 1.0)),\n        FrameConnectConfig(max_frame_gap=5),\n        DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2),\n        DensityFilterConfig(n_sigma=2.0),\n        RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno),\n    ],\n    outdir = \"output/\",\n    verbose = Verbosity.STANDARD\n)\n\n# image_stacks is Vector{Array}: 4 datasets, each (height, width, 2000)\n(result, info) = analyze(image_stacks, config)\n\nThe analyze function returns (AnalysisResult, AnalysisInfo) following the JuliaSMLM tuple-pattern. Each step produces diagnostic outputs in the output directory.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-1:-Detection-Fitting","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step 1: Detection + Fitting","text":"DetectFitConfig combines ROI detection (SMLMBoxer) and MLE fitting (GaussMLE) into a single step. For multi-dataset data (Vector{Array}), each dataset is processed independently.\n\nDetectFitConfig(\n    boxsize = 7,          # ROI size in pixels\n    min_photons = 500.0,  # Detection threshold\n    psf_sigma = 0.13,     # Expected PSF width (um)\n    psf_model = :variable, # :fixed, :variable, or :anisotropic\n)\n\nDataset boundaries come from the data structure: Vector{Array} of length 4 = 4 datasets.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Detection-overlay","page":"Tutorial","title":"Detection overlay","text":"Shows detected ROIs overlaid on raw camera frames. Yellow boxes mark each candidate molecule:\n\n(Image: Detection overlay)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Fit-overlay","page":"Tutorial","title":"Fit overlay","text":"Boxes colored by fit quality – green passes all filters, red fails photon threshold, orange fails precision, purple fails p-value:\n\n(Image: Fit overlay)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Fit-quality-distributions","page":"Tutorial","title":"Fit quality distributions","text":"Histograms of photons, background, localization precision, p-value, and PSF width. Gray regions show what would be rejected by the specified filter thresholds:\n\n(Image: Fit quality)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-2:-Filtering","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step 2: Filtering","text":"FilterConfig applies quality-based filtering. All criteria use (min, max) tuples:\n\nFilterConfig(\n    photons = (500.0, Inf),      # Minimum 500 photons\n    precision = (0.0, 0.007),    # Maximum 7nm precision\n    pvalue = (1e-3, 1.0),       # Goodness-of-fit threshold\n    psf_sigma = :auto            # Optional: mode +/- 10%\n)\n\nThe acceptance rate (typically 60-90% for well-optimized detection) is reported in the step summary.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-3:-Frame-Connection","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step 3: Frame Connection","text":"FrameConnectConfig links localizations of the same emitter across consecutive frames. This step also performs uncertainty calibration, comparing reported CRLB uncertainties against observed frame-to-frame scatter.\n\nFrameConnectConfig(\n    max_frame_gap = 5,      # Allow gaps of up to 5 dark frames\n    max_sigma_dist = 5.0,   # Spatial matching threshold\n    calibrate = true,     # Run uncertainty calibration\n    clamp_k_to_one = true # Don't allow k < 1 (CRLB is theoretical lower bound)\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Track-size-distribution","page":"Tutorial","title":"Track size distribution","text":"Shows the number of localizations per track. The mean track length reflects blinking kinetics (k_off):\n\n(Image: Track histogram)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Uncertainty-calibration","page":"Tutorial","title":"Uncertainty calibration","text":"Compares reported variance (CRLB) against observed variance from frame-to-frame scatter. The fit gives A (motion variance in nm^2) and B (CRLB scale factor):\n\n(Image: Uncertainty calibration)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Drift-jitter","page":"Tutorial","title":"Drift jitter","text":"Frame-to-frame position shifts estimated from linked emitters. Shows both instantaneous jitter and cumulative drift across all datasets:\n\n(Image: Drift jitter)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-4:-Drift-Correction","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step 4: Drift Correction","text":"DriftCorrectConfig corrects sample drift using entropy-based optimization from SMLMDriftCorrection.\n\nDriftCorrectConfig(\n    degree = 2,            # Polynomial degree\n    continuous = false,    # Registered mode (multi-dataset)\n    quality = :singlepass  # :singlepass or :iterative\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Drift-trajectory","page":"Tutorial","title":"Drift trajectory","text":"Shows the estimated X and Y drift over time and the XY path. For multi-dataset data, each dataset's trajectory is shown in a different color:\n\n(Image: Drift trajectory)\n\nFor details on continuous vs registered modes and chunking strategies, see the Guide.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-5:-Density-Filter","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step 5: Density Filter","text":"DensityFilterConfig removes isolated localizations that lack neighbors, which are likely false detections.\n\nDensityFilterConfig(\n    n_sigma = 2.0,           # Search radius in sigma units\n    min_neighbors = :auto    # Auto-detect threshold via valley method\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Neighbor-histogram","page":"Tutorial","title":"Neighbor histogram","text":"The valley between the isolated peak (low neighbors) and the clustered peak (high neighbors) determines the threshold:\n\n(Image: Neighbor histogram)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-6:-Render","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step 6: Render","text":"RenderConfig generates super-resolution images using SMLMRender. Multiple renders can be added as separate pipeline steps.\n\n# Gaussian blur rendering (publication quality)\nRenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno)\n\n# Histogram binning colored by time\nRenderConfig(strategy=HistogramRender(), zoom=10, colormap=:turbo, color_by=:absolute_frame)\n\n# Circle rendering colored by time\nRenderConfig(strategy=CircleRender(), zoom=50, colormap=:turbo, color_by=:absolute_frame)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Gaussian-render","page":"Tutorial","title":"Gaussian render","text":"(Image: Gaussian render)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Histogram-render","page":"Tutorial","title":"Histogram render","text":"(Image: Histogram render)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Circle-render","page":"Tutorial","title":"Circle render","text":"(Image: Circle render)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Step-by-Step-Workflow","page":"Tutorial","title":"Step-by-Step Workflow","text":"The analyze() dispatch enables iterative parameter tuning:\n\n# Run detection + fitting (expensive step)\n(smld, df_info) = analyze(image_stacks, DetectFitConfig(camera=camera, boxsize=7);\n    outdir=\"output/\", step_number=1, verbose=Verbosity.STANDARD)\nsmld_raw = df_info.smld_raw\n\n# Save for later resume\nsave_smld(\"output/after_detectfit.h5\", smld)\n\n# Try filter parameters\n(smld_filtered, _) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(500.0, Inf));\n    smld_raw=smld_raw, outdir=\"output/\", step_number=2, verbose=Verbosity.STANDARD)\n\n# Not happy? Try looser filter on same smld (no re-detection needed)\n(smld_filtered, _) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(300.0, Inf));\n    smld_raw=smld_raw)\n\n# Continue pipeline\n(smld_fc, fc_info) = analyze(smld_filtered, FrameConnectConfig(max_frame_gap=5))\n(smld_dc, dc_info) = analyze(smld_fc, DriftCorrectConfig(degree=2))\n(img, _) = analyze(smld_dc, RenderConfig(zoom=20, colormap=:inferno))\n\n# Resume from saved checkpoint in new session\nsmld = load_smld(\"output/after_detectfit.h5\")\n(smld, _) = analyze(smld, FilterConfig(photons=(400.0, Inf)))","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Output-Directory-Structure","page":"Tutorial","title":"Output Directory Structure","text":"When outdir is set, each step writes to a numbered subdirectory:\n\noutput/\n├── 01_detectfit/\n│   ├── config.toml\n│   ├── info.toml\n│   ├── stats.md\n│   ├── fit_quality.png\n│   ├── detection_overlay.png\n│   └── fit_overlay.png\n├── 02_filter/\n│   ├── config.toml\n│   └── stats.md\n├── 03_frameconnect/\n│   ├── config.toml\n│   ├── info.toml\n│   ├── stats.md\n│   ├── track_histogram.png\n│   ├── uncertainty_calibration.png\n│   └── drift_jitter.png\n├── 04_driftcorrect/\n│   ├── config.toml\n│   ├── info.toml\n│   ├── stats.md\n│   └── drift_trajectory.png\n├── 05_densityfilter/\n│   ├── config.toml\n│   ├── stats.md\n│   └── neighbor_histogram.png\n├── 06_render/\n│   ├── config.toml\n│   ├── info.toml\n│   └── gaussianrender_inferno_20x.png\n└── summary.md","category":"section"}]
}
